WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Welcome to the H&dM AI-Onboarding.

2
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:07.500
This first video will explain what Artificial Intelligence is,

3
00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:11.000
introduce a few basic AI terms,

4
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.000
and look at the most common ways AI is currently used at H&dM.

5
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.500
Artificial Intelligence, or AI, is a general-purpose technology.

6
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:23.000
That means it is not one single tool for one single task.

7
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Like electricity, computing, or the internet,
it can be applied across many different fields and workflows.

8
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:33.000
At a basic level, a so called 'AI model' is a trained software system

9
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:37.000
that analyzes large amounts of data, recognizes patterns,
and generates output.

10
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.500
These models do not learn in real-time, but have a cut-off date.

11
00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:45.000
This is why they need additional context
to give answers related to recent events.

12
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Depending on the task, AI can work in different ways.

13
00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Predictive AI helps estimate, classify, or analyze outcomes.

14
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:57.000
It can support tasks such as clustering information,
identifying patterns, or comparing options.

15
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:02.000
Generative AI creates new content, such as text, images,
code, video, diagrams, or sound.

16
00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:05.000
Agentic AI goes a step further:

17
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
it can use tools, follow multi-step instructions,
and support more complex workflows within defined limits.

18
00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:14.500
Today, most AI use at H&dM is generative AI,
together with some selected agentic use cases.

19
00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:19.000
The most common generative AI tools are Large Language Models,
or LLMs, such as ChatGPT.

20
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:23.500
These models are especially useful for drafting, summarizing,
translating, rephrasing,

21
00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:27.500
reviewing spelling and grammar,
and supporting early writing or coding tasks.

22
00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:31.000
Another important area is image generation and image enhancement.

23
00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:35.500
Image generation models, such as Nano Banana,
can support early visual exploration,

24
00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:40.000
mood boards, illustrative sketches, diagrams, or image enhancement.

25
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.000
We highly encourage you to explore the possibilities
of using AI in your daily work.

26
00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:49.500
AI can help us explore various designs, communicate more clearly,

27
00:01:49.500 --> 00:01:54.500
work more efficiently or even enable completely new skills
that are currently outside of our core expertise.

28
00:01:54.500 --> 00:01:57.500
But it also comes with risks and responsibilities.

29
00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:00.000
These are the focus of the next video.
